tly changing how your population reacts to certain policies, how much money you make/spend, and diplomatic changes.These feels EXTREMELY random, and sometimes, being bombarded by certain similar events one after another, seem unfair. It's more of a luck game, then a strategy game.Overall, the game is good, a 7/10. It's a basic country ruling simulator, that is a bit unforgiving at times, as it can sometimes throw constant situations and events at you that make it impossible to stay alive for more then 20 turns. If your into roleplaying as a leader, go for it.Similar games- Long Live the Queen.Unsimilar games-Bad Rats"
