76561198102896301,Not Recommended,396090,33751191,Posted: 23 July,all,peter.beketer,"Rogue State is a handsome mess. I've tried to like it, I spent on it 7 hours, and 12 more after some pause, and in the end I feel robbed.The game lets you feel like a ruler in terms of stress and management, but not in terms of making a difference. Sometimes the game doesn't seems to answer to your choices, sometimes it's misguiding/arbitrary, and sometimes it feels too cruel or even too sugared.About choises:You can disallow the death penalty and give amnesty to previous ruler's allies, but anyway NPCs will say that you executed them publicly, and sometimes the game will obliviously suggest to punish your subordinates with nonexistent measure.Random regular events – one of important gameplay features – contributes to the feeling of powerless. Event can ask you to deal with, say, ecological problem, and the only way to resolve it... is to encounter this crisis not before X turn. Not before you'll be allowed to build infrastructure, because you need will to have specific construction. That could add some drama or 'realism', but you can never solve crisis later, not even for a month, and it doesn't always makes any sense.About misguiding:You can lose the game while having 100% approval of every person and institute in the county just because pretty UI doesn't helps you to understand objectives. It feels like cheating, and the game cheats you repeatedly. After every walkthrough you'll earn some XP to unlock new gameplay features. Unfortunately, some of them are mediocre, and others just have no effect (literally).About cruelty or sugary:It's just another form of inability to play as you want. You can build liberal paradise, but your subordinates will anyway fail to interrogate prisoner without killing him, because it is mentioned in a dialogue, and dialogues doesn't react on your play-style, they all written for default ""dirty heartless dictator"" style. Sweetness is the opposite: if you wish to be a strict ruler, you can forbid hamburgers or western haircuts, but the most severe measure you can inflict on liberal manifestation is... turning blind eye on it.I'm afraid that Rogue State actually has only one real way to win it, a pretty precise set of steps. Any other steps are of no significance or wrong. It's not awful – many components of the game are very decent – but I can't recommend it."
